<h3><b>5. Promote During the Event</b></h3>
<p>Donâ€™t stop marketing once the event starts. Use social media to share live updates, photos, or even stream parts of the event. This keeps attendees engaged and creates FOMO (fear of missing out) for those who didnâ€™t attend, which is great for future events.</p>
<h3><b>6. Measure Success and Gather Feedback</b></h3>
<p>Finally, after the event, evaluate its success by looking at key metrics like attendance, lead generation, and social media engagement. Also, get feedback from attendees to see what worked and what didnâ€™t. This insight will be invaluable for your next event. But how to do all of the â€œafter-eventsâ€ effort? Here&#8217;s a checklist format for measuring success and gathering feedback after events:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Track Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</b>
<ul>
<li>Compare registered vs. actual attendees, analyse no-show rates, and ticket sales data.</li>
<li>Evaluate total revenue against the event budget and expenses.</li>
<li>Measure interaction through social media mentions, app usage, and session participation.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Conduct Post-Event Surveys</b>
<ul>
<li>Distribute surveys to gather feedback on content, speakers, and overall experience.</li>
<li>Calculate Net Promoter Score (NPS) to determine how likely attendees are to recommend your event to others.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Analyse Social Media Engagement</b>
<ul>
<li>Monitor social media for event mentions and hashtag use.</li>
<li>Review engagement metrics like likes, shares, comments, and reach.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Review Event Technology Reports</b>
<ul>
<li>Check app usage statistics, including logins, feature usage, and session attendance.</li>
<li>Analyse website traffic patterns, peak visit times, and popular content.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Hold a Debrief Meeting</b>
<ul>
<li>Discuss what went well and areas for improvement with your team.</li>
<li>Gather input from stakeholders, sponsors, and partners.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Collect and Analyse Qualitative Feedback</b>
<ul>
<li>Engage with attendees for real-time reactions and suggestions.</li>
<li>Review unsolicited feedback or testimonials for additional insights.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>Follow Up with Attendees</b>
<ul>
<li>Send personalised thank you messages and request additional feedback if needed.</li>
<li>Share highlights, photos, and key takeaways, and invite further comments or suggestions.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Use this checklist to ensure you comprehensively measure your event&#8217;s success and gather meaningful feedback.</p>
<h3><b>Event Apps to Simplify Your Event Marketing</b></h3>
